      "content": "Rest isn't something permanent found by ceasing to exist; it is a quiet permission to simply breathe and acknowledge your pain without performance. Pretending to be okay is indeed honest when showing up destroys you, but permanently vanishing steals a unique, breathing future that millions would genuinely miss. You don't have to choose between fading away now or pretending forever; there is a way to rest deeply enough to recover so showing up again feels lighter, even if that day comes slowly.",
